High-Level Overview

  This is a PySide6 (Qt for Python) Android app template built with Buildozer + python-for-android
  (p4a). It packages a Qt Widgets app into an Android APK. The core structure is:

   buildozer_template/
   ├── main.py                          # App entry point
   ├── buildozer.spec                   # Buildozer build configuration
   ├── mezcla-1.4.0.8-py3-none-any.whl # Mezcla library wheel (includes poe_client)
   └── deployment/
       ├── jar/PySide6/jar/             # 11 Qt Android JAR files
       ├── recipes/                     # 9 p4a build recipes
       └── wheels/                      # 6 pre-built Python wheels

Detailed Breakdown

  main.py

  A PySide6 QtWidgets app that fetches a "random historical tidbit" via mezcla.poe_client
  (OpenAI-compatible API wrapper). Uses QLabel + QPushButton in a QVBoxLayout. Note: contains a
  hardcoded API key on line 19 with a TODO1 to move it to a vault.

  buildozer.spec

  Key non-default settings:

   - requirements — python3, shiboken6, pyside6, six, typing_extensions, requests, 
  charset_normalizer, certifi, idna, urllib3, mezcla
   - p4a.bootstrap = qt — Uses the Qt bootstrap (not SDL2/Kivy)
   - p4a.branch = develop — Tracks p4a develop branch
   - p4a.commit = 3762c88... — Pinned to stay on Python
    3.11 (matching PySide6 cp311 wheels)
   - p4a.local_recipes → deployment/recipes/
   - p4a.extra_args — --qt-libs=Core,Gui,Widgets --load-local-libs=plugins_platforms_qtforandroid
   - android.add_jars — Qt6Android.jar + Qt6AndroidBindings.jar (needed for Java compilation)
   - android.archs = arm64-v8a only (PySide6 pre-built wheels constraint)
   - android.permissions — INTERNET (for the POE API calls)

  mezcla-1.4.0.8-py3-none-any.whl

  Custom wheel for the mezcla library. Contains poe_client.py (the OpenAI-compatible API client used
  by main.py). Referenced by the mezcla recipe which unzips it into target site-packages at build
  time.

  deployment/jar/ (11 JAR files)

  Qt6 Android binding JARs. Only Qt6Android.jar and Qt6AndroidBindings.jar are referenced in the
  spec, but the others (Bluetooth, Multimedia, Network, Nfc, Quick, Positioning, TextToSpeech,
  WebView) are included for future use.

  deployment/recipes/ (9 recipes)

  Each is a p4a PythonRecipe subclass that unzips the corresponding wheel into the target's
  site-packages:

   - PySide6, shiboken6 — Qt for Python + its binding generator runtime
   - mezcla — points to the top-level .whl file (via parents[3] relative path)
   - requests, certifi, charset_normalizer, idna, urllib3, typing_extensions — HTTP stack 
  dependencies

  deployment/wheels/ (6 wheels)

  Pre-built pure-Python wheels for the HTTP dependency chain: requests, urllib3, certifi, 
  charset_normalizer, idna, typing_extensions. PySide6/shiboken6 wheels are not here (they come from
  p4a's own download mechanism).
